Form of causal modeling that fit networks of constructs to data

This article delves into the general realm of [structural modeling](/Structural_equation_modeling). For the specific application of structural models within the domain of [econometrics](/Econometrics), a field often preoccupied with the quantitative analysis of economic phenomena, one should consult the article on [Structural estimation](/Structural_estimation). Furthermore, for those seeking the academic publication dedicated to this intricate subject, information can be found under the entry for [Structural Equation Modeling (journal)](/Structural_Equation_Modeling_(journal)).

